goetzeindia.net","city":"Gurugram","full_time_employees":2599,"trailing_pe":11.668718,"price_to_book":1.5516608,"book_value":244.48,"eps_trailing":32.51,"payout_ratio":0.0,"revenue":19490146304.0,"revenue_per_share":350.168,"revenue_growth":0.144,"ebitda":3468214528.0,"ebitda_margins":0.17795,"gross_margins":0.62796,"operating_margins":0.09389,"profit_margins":0.092819996,"net_income":1809159936.0,"total_cash":6569726976.0,"total_cash_per_share":118.037,"total_debt":20562000.0,"debt_to_equity":0.143,"enterprise_value":15330614272.0,"enterprise_to_ebitda":4.42,"enterprise_to_revenue":0.787,"earnings_growth":0.004,"shares_outstanding":55632130.0,"float_shares":13923465.0,"held_pct_insiders":0.78132004,"held_pct_institutions":0.00328,"beta":-0.091,"fifty_two_week_high":622.0,"fifty_two_week_low":319.65,"fifty_day_average":420.367,"two_hundred_day_avg":492.6045,"recommendation":"none","all_time_high":666.45,"all_time_low":17.0,"long_business_summary":"Federal-Mogul Goetze (India) Limited manufactures, supply, and distributes automotive components for two/three/four-wheeler automobiles in India and internationally. It provides pistons, piston rings, and wet and dry cylinder liners for a range of applications, including bi-wheelers, passenger cars, SUVs, tractors, light and heavy commercial vehicles, locomotive engines, stationary engines, and high output locomotive diesel engines. The company also offers sintered metal products for various engines and automotive applications, such as valve trains, transmission, lubrication pumps, and other engine/structural parts. It exports its products. The company was formerly known as Goetze (India) Limited and changed its name to Federal-Mogul Goetze (India) Limited in 2006. The company was incorporated in 1954 and is based in Gurugram, India. Federal-Mogul Goetze (India) Limited is a subsidiary of Federal Mogul Holding Limited."}}